  "url": "https://www.ada.lk/breaking_news/\u0dc1\u0dca\u200d\u0dbb\u0dd3-\u0dbd\u0d82\u0d9a\u0dcf\u0dc0-\u0db6\u0d82\u0d9a\u0ddc\u0dbd\u0ddc\u0dad\u0dca\u0dc0\u0dd3\u0db8\u0da7-\u0da0\u0dd3\u0db1-\u0dab\u0dba-\u0dc4\u0dcf-\u0dc0\u0dca\u200d\u0dba\u0dcf\u0db4\u0dd8\u0dad\u0dd2-\u0dc4\u0dda\u0dad\u0dd4\u0dc0\u0d9a\u0dca-\u0db1\u0dd9\u0db8\u0dd9\u0dba\u0dd2/11-395853",
  "time_ut": 1659089874,
  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0dc1\u0dca\u200d\u0dbb\u0dd3 \u0dbd\u0d82\u0d9a\u0dcf\u0dc0 \u0db6\u0d82\u0d9a\u0ddc\u0dbd\u0ddc\u0dad\u0dca\u0dc0\u0dd3\u0db8\u0da7 \u0da0\u0dd3\u0db1 \u0dab\u0dba \u0dc4\u0dcf \u0dc0\u0dca\u200d\u0dba\u0dcf\u0db4\u0dd8\u0dad\u0dd2 \u0dc4\u0dda\u0dad\u0dd4\u0dc0\u0d9a\u0dca \u0db1\u0dd9\u0db8\u0dd9\u0dba\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Chinese loans and projects are not the reason for Sri Lanka's bankruptcy",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "China rejected the allegation made by Samantha Power of the United States that one of the main reasons for Sri Lanka's bankruptcy was opaque loans and unproductive projects by China.",
        "China's Ministry of Foreign Affairs spokesman Zhao Lijian said that the economic development of Sri Lanka increased through the development projects implemented by China in Sri Lanka.",
        "\"China-Sri Lanka practical cooperation has always been conducted by Sri Lanka based on scientific plans and has nothing to do with full verification,\" Chinese Foreign Ministry spokesperson said at the daily press conference.",
        "\"Chinese projects have boosted Sri Lanka's economic development and brought tangible benefits to the Sri Lankan people,\" he said. Rejecting Samantha Power's allegations, Zhao said, \"Sri Lanka's foreign debt has multiple components, and China-related debt is a much smaller share than international capital markets and multilateral development banks.\" Namely.",
        "\"China has provided Sri Lanka with low interest rates and long-term preferential loans, which have played a positive role in improving Sri Lanka's infrastructure and livelihoods,\" he said.",
        "He also said that US policies, including interest rate hikes, unilateral sanctions and massive stimulus policies, which have seriously affected many developing countries such as Sri Lanka, are the cause of the world economic crisis.",
        "\"The recent sudden interest rate hikes in the United States have caused great damage to global economic and financial markets,\" he noted.",
        "\"Rising prices of energy, food and other commodities have worsened through US unilateral sanctions and tariff barriers. This has further aggravated the financial and economic situation of many developing countries, including Sri Lanka.\" He said."
      ],
